{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"title":"Sponge cake","content":["Preheat oven to 180°C. Grease a spring form cake tin (Ø 20 cm).","Place almonds and buckwheat in mixing bowl then grind <nobr>10 sec\/speed 7<\/nobr>. Transfer to a large bowl and set aside.","Place carrots in mixing bowl and chop <nobr>8 sec\/speed 6<\/nobr>. Transfer to bowl with almonds and set aside.","Place eggs, honey, sugar, salt and orange peel in mixing bowl then mix <nobr>5 sec\/speed 7<\/nobr>.","Add maize flour, baking powder and reserved almond-buckwheat-carrot mixture then mix <nobr>15 sec\/speed 5<\/nobr>. Transfer dough to prepared cake tin and bake for 30-35 minutes (180°C) until skewer inserted in centre comes out clean. Meanwhile, clean mixing bowl.","Leave cake to cool in tin for 10 minutes then remove and transfer to a wire rack to cool completely."]},{"title":"Topping","content":[" <strong>Insert butterfly whisk<\/strong>. Place cream in mixing bowl and whisk, without measuring cup, <nobr>1 min - 1 min 30 sec\/speed 3<\/nobr> until softly whipped.","Add orange liqueur and honey then whisk <nobr>30 sec\/speed 3<\/nobr>. <strong>Remove butterfly whisk<\/strong>.","Spread icing over top of cake and scatter with extra orange zest for decoration. Store cake in fridge and serve chilled."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"Sponge cake","content":["butter for greasing","200 g almonds","30 g buckwheat grains","250 g carrots, in pieces","3 medium eggs","100 g honey","100 g golden caster sugar","1 pinch fine sea salt","½ orange, thin peelings of skin only, plus extra zest for garnish","70 g maize flour","½ tsp baking powder"]},{"title":"Topping","content":["250 g double cream","1 - 1 ½ Tbsp orange liqueur","20 g runny honey"]}],"id":"r101849","imageLink":"https:\/\/1.bp.blogspot.com\/-XCn8qv6Jcbk\/XZWqtJ7QGMI\/AAAAAAAAfcE\/en-XL8i0FHEmRRnCy2JvYM9US0aUIhuJgCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_T6cp27-zAx39mjin.png","title":"Gluten Free Carrot and Orange Cake","publishedAt":"2016-05-09T00:00:00Z","nutrition